SIMPLE: fecundity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fecundity
<hw>Fe*cun"di*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fecunditas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>f⟦eacute⟧condit⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See
<er>Fecund</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or power of
producing fruit; fruitfulness; especially <fld>(Biol.)</fld>, the
quality in female organisms of reproducing rapidly and in great
numbers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The power of germinating; as in seeds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The power of bringing forth in abundance; fertility;
richness of invention; <as>as, the <ex>fecundity</ex> of God's creative
power</as>.</def> <rj><au>Bentley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fed</ent>⟦br⟧
